<p>Create a form that runs the following code.</p>  <pre><code>MsgBox (VBE.ActiveCodePane.CodeModule) </code></pre>  <p>And this message appears.</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/tTIF5.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/tTIF5.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>Now save, close, and reopen the database, and see this message:</p>  <p>Run-time error '91': Object variable or With block variable not set</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/YXT8f.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/YXT8f.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>If you open the Visual Basic Editor, it runs again. Even if you close the VBE, it still runs.</p>  <p>But when you close the whole application and reopen it, leaving the VBE closed, you get the error.</p>  <p>Why? What's going on here?</p>